Here's my suggestion for the dealing with the TimeZone issue:
protected static TimeZone defaultTimeZone;

@BeforeClass
public static void setupTimeZone() {
    defaultTimeZone = TimeZone.getDefault();
    TimeZone.setDefault(TimeZone.getTimeZone("UTC"));
}

@AfterClass
public static void resetTimeZone() {
    TimeZone.setDefault(defaultTimeZone);
}
PS It maybe worth looking into creating a BaseFhirNarrativeTest class which handles:

Creating the context and parser (i.e., the @Before method with both the ctx and parser fields marked as protected
Setting up the timezone stuff suggested above

